TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {5841=Jay-Z has undertaken plenty of musical endeavors in the last calendar year, but you wouldn't know it based on recent headlines. In fact, his nine nominations at the 2014 Grammy Awards – more than any other artist – is barely a footnote when you consider the current reasons tongues are wagging about the rap superstar., 2644=Away from the mic, Jay-Z has plenty of other things to keep him busy. He co-owns a chain of sports bars known as the 40/40 Club, has a minority stake in the NBA's Brooklyn Nets and the co-creator of the clothing line Rocawear. He also founded the sports agency Roc Nation Sports, and is a certified sports agent. Most talked about, however, is his personal life. He married R&B superstar Beyonce Knowles in 2008. They had a daughter named Blue Ivy Carter in January 2012., 5029=In early May, Jay-Z was part of a one-sided brawl when Solange attacked him in an elevator at a New York hotel. Leaked surveillance footage that has been played countless times on television and online show him deflecting the blows, but otherwise making no aggressive moves to counter the attack. Still, his reputation appeared in question and was unceremoniously dragged through the mud until a joint statement was issued proclaiming that Jay-Z, Beyonce and Solange had moved past the incident.}
